ory\"] by Tony Drovetto ''seahawks.com'' (December 23, 2015) Retrieved December 12, 2019</ref> They married on May 27, 2017 in Seattle.<ref>[https://www.instagram.com/p/Bx-WcsggH0n/ \"kj_wright34\"] ''[[Instagram]]'' (May 27, 2019) Retrieved December 12, 2019</ref> The couple has two sons. The Wrights were featured in the December 11, 2019 ''[[House Hunters]]'' episode \"Big Ballin' in Seattle\".<ref>[https://www.instagram.com/p/B55c_LygekI/ \"kj_wright34\"] ''[[Instagram]]'' Retrieved December 12, 2019</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.kjwright50.com KJ Wright Official Website]\n* {{Twitter}}\n* [https://www.instagram.com/kj_wright34/ KJ Wright Official Instagram]\n* {{Football stats |nfl=2495252 |espn=14140 |pfr=W/WrigK.00}}\n* [http://www.mstateathletics.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=16800&ATCLID=1087911 Mississippi State Bulldogs bio]\n\n{{Seahawks2011DraftPicks}}\n{{Super Bowl XLVIII}}\n{{Seattle Seahawks roster navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wright, K. J.}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:African-American players of American football]]\n[[Category:American football linebackers]]\n[[Category:Mississippi State Bulldogs football players]]\n[[Category:National Conference Pro Bowl players]]\n[[Category:People from Olive Branch, Mississippi]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Mississippi]]\n[[Category:Seattle Seahawks players]]\n[[Category:Super Bowl champions]]\n", "name_user": "PNWEJ", "label": "safe", "comment": "Removal of Gus Bradley as Defensive Coordinator for 2013 Seahawk's Defense.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K._J._Wright"}
